---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const updated = "27 June 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Rosewood Living"
  description="How Rosewood Living collects, uses, stores and protects the personal information you share with us, in line with the Australian Privacy Principles."
>
  <Nav />

  <main>
    <!-- HEADER -->
    <section class="border-b border-line bg-surface">
      <div class="u-container pb-[clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4rem)] pt-36">
        <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
        <h1 class="mt-6 text-h1 font-display" style="font-weight:500">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-[0.9rem] uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-muted">
          Last updated {updated}
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- BODY -->
    <section class="py-[clamp(3rem,6vw,5rem)]">
      <div class="u-container">
        <article class="legal max-w-3xl">
          <p>
            Rosewood Living (&ldquo;Rosewood Living&rdquo;, &ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo; or
            &ldquo;our&rdquo;) is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains how we
            collect, use, disclose and safeguard your personal information when you visit our
            website or engage our services, and how we comply with the
            <em>Privacy Act 1988</em> (Cth) and the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs).
          </p>
          <p>
            By using this website or submitting an enquiry or Letter of Intent request, you
            consent to the collection and use of your information as described below.
          </p>

          <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
          <p>We only collect information that is reasonably necessary for our functions and activities, including:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Contact details</strong> — your name, role, company, email address and phone number.</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Project details</strong> — information you provide about a development site,
              such as the project address, development type, dwelling numbers and related figures.
            </li>
            <li><strong>Correspondence</strong> — any messages, enquiries or documents you send us.</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Technical data</strong> — limited information your browser shares automatically,
              such as your IP address, device and general usage, used to keep the site secure and reliable.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>2. How we use your information</h2>
          <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>respond to your enquiries and prepare and issue your Letter of Intent;</li>
            <li>provide our advisory and management services and communicate with you about them;</li>
            <li>maintain our records and meet our regulatory and reporting obligations as a community housing provider; and</li>
            <li>improve, secure and operate our website.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We will not use your information for an unrelated purpose without your consent, unless
            permitted or required by law.
          </p>

          <h2>3. Disclosure of your information</h2>
          <p>
            We do not sell your personal information. We may disclose it to trusted service
            providers who help us operate our business — for example, secure cloud hosting,
            database and email delivery providers — and only so they can perform services on our
            behalf. We may also disclose information where required or authorised by law, or to
            protect our legal rights.
          </p>

          <h2>4. Storage and security</h2>
          <p>
            Your information is stored on reputable third-party platforms that may process or store
            data in Australia or overseas. We take reasonable steps to protect your information from
            misuse, loss and unauthorised access, including access controls and encrypted
            connections. No method of transmission over the internet is completely secure, and we
            cannot guarantee absolute security.
          </p>

          <h2>5. Retention</h2>
          <p>
            We keep personal information only for as long as it is needed for the purposes described
            in this policy, or as required to meet our legal and regulatory obligations, after which
            we take reasonable steps to delete or de-identify it.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
          <p>
            You may request access to the personal information we hold about you, and ask us to
            correct it if it is inaccurate, out of date or incomplete. To make a request, or if you
            have a privacy concern, contact us using the details below. We will respond within a
            reasonable period. If you are not satisfied with our response, you may contact the
            Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC) at
            <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener">oaic.gov.au</a>.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Cookies and analytics</h2>
          <p>
            Our website uses minimal cookies and similar technologies that are necessary for the
            site to function and to understand general usage. You can control or disable cookies
            through your browser settings; some features may not work as intended if you do.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Third-party links</h2>
          <p>
            Our website may contain links to external sites that we do not operate. We are not
            responsible for the privacy practices of those sites and encourage you to review their
            policies.
          </p>

          <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The current version will always be
            available on this page, with the &ldquo;last updated&rdquo; date revised accordingly.
          </p>

          <h2>10. Contact us</h2>
          <p>
            For any privacy questions or requests, please contact:
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Rosewood Living</strong><br />
            238 Victoria Rd, Gladesville NSW 2111, Australia<br />
            Email: <a href="mailto:info@rosewoodliving.com.au">info@rosewoodliving.com.au</a><br />
            ABN 11 142 441 549
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .legal {
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  .legal > p:first-child {
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: var(--text-h3);
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin-top: 2.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  }
  .legal p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.78;
  }
  .legal ul {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    padding-left: 1.15rem;
    list-style: disc;
  }
  .legal li {
    margin-bottom: 0.55rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .legal a {
    color: var(--color-rosewood);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .legal a:hover {
    color: var(--color-rosewood-deep);
  }
  .legal strong {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .legal em {
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
